Truth Table

I. Conditional AND (&&) Operator
	ex: if(gpa >= 3.5 && playsSports == true) {
			S.O.P("Is a Scholar Athlete);
		} 
	
	expression 1		expression 2		exp1 & exp2
		F					F					F
		F					T					F
		T					F					F
		T					T					T
		
II. Conditional OR (||) Operator
	 ex: if((SemAvg >= 40) || (finalExam) >= 90)) {
			 S.O.P("Student grade is A");
		 }
	
	expression 1		expression 2		exp1 & exp2
		F					F					F
		F					T					T
		T					F					T
		T					T					T
		
III. Exclusive OR (^) Operator
	  *Is true if and only if one of its operands is true and the other false
	  
	  expression 1		expression 2		exp1 & exp2
		F					F					F
		F					T					T
		T					F					T
		T					T					F
		
IV. Logical Negation (!) Operator
	 ex: if(password != sentinelValue) {
	 	S.O.P("Try again dumbass!");
	 	 } 
					OR
		if(!(password == sentinelValue)) {
	 	S.O.P("Try again dumbass!");
	 	 } 
	 	 
	 	expression 1		expression 2
	 		F					T
	 		T					F

V. DeMorgan's Law 
	* express logical expressions in different ways (usually to make it convenient for us)
	 ex: !(condition1 && condition2)
	 		is same as 
	 	 (!condition1 || !condition2)
	 	 	and can be re-expressed as 
	 	 (!condition1 && !condition2)
	